      "content": "From a purely logical standpoint, ignoring the national debt is fiscally irresponsible because compounding interest and future servicing costs eventually become a massive drag on government spending. A country with unsustainable debt levels faces a real risk of sovereign debt crises or needing drastic, painful austerity measures later. Therefore, prioritizing fiscal discipline and debt reduction is a necessary foundation for long-term economic stability.",
