    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that seems fair, but then people on the other side say that social spending actually helps the economy grow in the long run by keeping people healthy and educated. if a government just focuses on debt and cuts all the social stuff, aren't they kind of sabotaging the very growth they need to pay the debt back? how do you balance that without just picking one side?",
