      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The core of the issue is that social spending can be an investment, but only if it is funded sustainably. If spending cuts lead to a collapse in human capital—through poor health or low education—then the economy *will* stagnate, making debt repayment impossible. The logical balance involves finding efficiencies within social programs while simultaneously enacting credible, structural reforms to reduce the debt burden. This requires a disciplined approach to both fiscal health and human capital investment.",
